# ohlc2intraday

Generate synthetic intraday price paths from daily OHLC data,
based on Riedel (2021) "The Value of the High, Low and Close 
in the Estimation of Brownian Motion".

## Motivation

Academic finance research often requires intraday data (TAQ, Bloomberg, etc.)
that costs $$$/year. Individual researchers and students can only access
free daily data (Yahoo Finance). This package bridges the gap by generating
statistically plausible intraday paths conditioned on daily OHLC.

## Status

Under active development (Phase 0).

- [x] Project structure
- [ ] Section 2: Basic Brownian bridge (close-only condition)
- [ ] Section 3: Close + High conditioning
- [ ] Section 4: Full OHLC conditioning
- [ ] Validation against FirstRateData ground truth
- [ ] PyPI release

## Reference

Riedel, K. (2021). The Value of the High, Low and Close 
in the Estimation of Brownian Motion. 
*Statistical Inference for Stochastic Processes.*
[arXiv:1911.05280](https://arxiv.org/abs/1911.05280)

